        <div n="506-09G1" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">T</hi>HE greatest Monarch may be stabb'd by Night,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-2"> And Fortune help the Murd'rer in his Flight;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-3"> The vilest Ruffian may commit a Rape,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-4"> Yet safe from injured Innocence escape;</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-5"> And Calumny, by working under Ground,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-6"> Can, unreveng'd, the greatest Merit wound.</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="7" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-7">W<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">HAT'S</hi> to be done? shall Wit and learning chuse,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-8"> To live obscure, and have no Fame to lose?</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-9"> By Censure frighted out of Honour's Road,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-10"> Nor dare to use the Gifts by Heav'n bestow'd;</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-11"> Or fearless enter in thro' Virtue's Gate,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-506-09G1-line-12"> And buy Distinction at the dearest Rate.506-09G1   </l></lg></div>
